HEADWORD: Wind-sucking
<hw>Wind"-suck`ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Far.)</fld> <def>A vicious
habit of a horse, consisting in the swallowing of air; -- usually
associated with crib-biting, or cribbing. See <er>Cribbing</er>,
4.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

